I don't think that you need to get RichMember, you can use
perunBl.getUsersManagerBl().getUserByMember(sess, member);
But when I think about it more, this whole solution is missing connection between created sponsored account in perun and login/učo. Like when it partially fails, then caller doesn't know, where to start again, when he sends only list of "names" to the API and there is no connection between that name and returned UČO. So you would have to query perun or password backend again to give you what was done and where to start again.

